documents.content:
{
  "id": "<scene id>",
  "title": "...",
  "description": "...",
  "steps": [
    {
      "label": "step description",
      "tool": "studio.chrome.select_tab",
      "args": {"key": "..."},
      "settleMs": 500,
      "overlay": [{"type": "highlight", "target": "<widget id>", "text": "..."}]
    }
  ]
}

step.tool = any MCP tool (studio.* / vibe_* / app_builder.*). studio.scenario.run dispatches each step, waits for settle, applies overlay, then advances to the next step.

When authored by an external LLM — write to disk with studio.scenario.save, validate each step with studio.scenario.preview, then verify actual execution with run.
